U.K. Tourist, Other Visits Rose `Substantially' in April

-- B y   J e n n i f e r   R y a n
-- 
2011-06-09T08:30:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-09/u-k-tourist-other-visits-rose-substantially-in-april.html
Visits to the U.K. by tourists
and other travelers rose “‘substantially” in April, the
monthPrince William married  Kate Middleton , from the
previous year.  Visits rose to 2.66 million people, the Office for
National Statistics said today in  London , without giving a
year-earlier figure. Travel a year earlier was disrupted by
the  ash cloud  from the Icelandic volcano.  In the three months through April, visits to the U.K.
increased 4 percent to 7.7 million compared with the
previous three months. In the same period, earnings from
overseas visits rose 3 percent to 4.2 billion pounds.  The April 29 wedding at Westminster Abbey in London
was seen by a U.S. television audience of 22.8 million
viewers, according to Nielson Co. data. U.K. retail sales
surged the most in five years the month of the ceremony,
according to the  British Retail Consortium . Britons
received a second four-day weekend to mark the
celebrations, which were accompanied by the warmest April
on record.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jennifer Ryan in London at 
